From 8867a020f00feb9a4280ec64d324a00be3753a00 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Sen Wang <sen@ti.com>
Date: Wed, 11 Mar 2026 23:17:00 -0500
Subject: [PATCH 4/5] arm64: dts: ti: k3-am62d-evm: Add TAS67CD-AEC daughter
 card overlay

Add device tree overlay for the TAS67CD-AEC daughter card on the
AM62D2-EVM via Audio Expansion Connector 1 (AEC1).

Use audio-graph-card2 with DPCM topology:

  FE0 (playback) -> BE0 (TAS0 main audio ch 1-4)
                 -> BE1 (TAS0 ANC bypass ch 1-4)
                 -> BE2 (TAS1 main audio ch 1-4)
                 -> BE3 (TAS1 ANC bypass ch 1-4)
  -----------------------------------------------
  FE1 (capture)  -> BE4 (TAS0 Isense & Vpredict)
                 -> BE5 (TAS1 Isense & Vpredict)

In the future, if McASP supports multi-stream, the main audio and
ANC bypass paths can be separated into distinct playback front-ends,
eliminating the need for an upmixer to mix in ANC data:

  FE0 (playback) -> BE0 (TAS0 main audio ch 1-4)
                 -> BE2 (TAS1 main audio ch 1-4)
  -----------------------------------------------
  FE1 (playback) -> BE1 (TAS0 ANC bypass ch 1-4)
                 -> BE3 (TAS1 ANC bypass ch 1-4)
  -----------------------------------------------
  FE2 (capture)  -> BE4 (TAS0 Isense & Vpredict)
                 -> BE5 (TAS1 Isense & Vpredict)

The codec driver can also interface with simple-audio-card using
only the main audio path (DAI 0).

Since ANC bypass is enabled and all TAS0/1 playback routes to one
AXR pin, 16 TDM slots are needed, which creates challenges for
McASP to provide adequate clock dividers for 44.1 kHz and 48 kHz
as the bus clock master (23k-56k ppm). A different HCLK source
frequency is needed; 96 MHz is not sufficient.

Signed-off-by: Sen Wang <sen@ti.com>
